<%- include('partials/header') %>

<!-- ============ ZONE 1 — THE HOOK ============ -->
<section class="hero" id="hero">
  <div class="grain"></div>
  <div class="hero__inner">
    <div class="hero__content">
      <p class="eyebrow">WRITTEN BY AN FMF NAVY CORPSMAN</p>
      <hr class="rule rule--short" />

      <h1 class="hero__title">
        <span class="fade-up" style="--d:0.05s">A CORPSMAN'S GUIDE TO</span>
        <span class="fade-up" style="--d:0.18s">LISTENING TO YOUR NERVOUS SYSTEM.</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="hero__sub fade-up" style="--d:0.32s">
        The war within finally has a field manual.
      </p>

      <p class="hero__body fade-up" style="--d:0.42s">
        Six Pillars. Seven Tools. 30 days. A field-tested nervous system protocol
        created by a Navy FMF Corpsman who spent 18 years struggling with PTSD. <strong>$27.</strong>
      </p>

      <div class="hero__cta fade-up" style="--d:0.52s">
        <a href="/checkout" class="btn btn--primary">GET THE MANUAL — $27</a>
        <a href="#mechanism" class="btn btn--ghost">SEE HOW IT WORKS</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero__cover fade-up" style="--d:0.4s">
      <img
        class="book-cover"
        src="/images/book-cover.png"
        width="1027" height="1531"
        alt="Book cover: The Nervous System Field Manual — A Corpsman's Guide to the War Within, by Bobby L. Harris. Battlefield Essentials."
        fetchpriority="high"
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ AUTHORITY BAR ============ -->
<section class="authority">
  <div class="authority__track">
    <span class="authority__item"><span class="authority__icon">★</span> FMF Navy Corpsman</span>
    <span class="authority__sep">|</span>
    <span class="authority__item"><span class="authority__icon">⚕</span> OEF Veteran</span>
    <span class="authority__sep">|</span>
    <span class="authority__item"><span class="authority__icon">▮</span> 18 Years of Field Testing</span>
    <span class="authority__sep">|</span>
    <span class="authority__item"><span class="authority__icon">✚</span> PTSD Recovery Survivor</span>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ ZONE 2 — THE MIRROR ============ -->
<section class="section mirror-section reveal" id="mirror">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <p class="label">THE REALITY</p>
    <h2 class="display">You Did Everything Right. Your Body Didn't Get the Memo.</h2>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        You've done everything right on paper. You showed up to the appointments. You took the
        medications they offered and waited six weeks to find out they flattened everything without
        fixing anything. You sat in the chair, told the story again, gained the insight, and walked
        out with the same body you walked in with — still braced, still scanning, still wired for a
        threat that isn't there anymore. You've cycled through enough providers that you've stopped
        expecting anything new. And somewhere underneath the exhaustion, you've started to wonder if
        this is just who you are now — if something in you got permanently altered, and the rest of
        your life is just managing it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <p class="label" style="margin-top:40px">ALMOST.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        In 2023 you finally got a diagnosis — a real one, with structure and language that fit — and
        for about a week it felt like the beginning of something, until you realized a name for the
        weight doesn't make it lighter.
      </p>
    </div>

    <blockquote class="pullquote">
      The diagnosis isn't wrong. The approach is.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Talk therapy and medication are top-down interventions — they work through the thinking mind,
        and your nervous system doesn't live there. Your nervous system isn't broken. It was trained.
        Precisely, effectively, and successfully trained — for an environment that no longer exists.
        That's not a defect. That's a mismatch. And mismatches can be corrected.
      </p>
      <p><strong>Here's what correcting it actually feels like:</strong></p>
    </div>

    <ul class="checklist">
      <% const correcting = [
        'Waking up without running a threat assessment of your own bedroom before your feet hit the floor',
        'Sitting in a crowded room without every exit already mapped and every person already categorized',
        'Feeling your shoulders drop — not because you told yourself to relax, but because your system actually stopped bracing',
        'Having a hard conversation without your body treating it like a contact engagement',
        'Sleeping through a noise that isn\'t a threat, because your nervous system finally knows the difference'
      ]; %>
      <% correcting.forEach(function(c){ %>
        <li class="check reveal"><span class="check__mark">✓</span><span><%= c %></span></li>
      <% }); %>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ ZONE 3 — THE MECHANISM ============ -->
<section class="section mechanism-section reveal" id="mechanism">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="label">THE MECHANISM</p>
    <h2 class="display">We Go Straight to the Body.</h2>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        While everyone else tries to reach the nervous system through the mind — through reflection,
        reframing, and cognitive insight — we go straight to the body, because the nervous system
        processes sensation before it processes language, and you cannot think your way out of a
        state your body is still physically holding.
      </p>
    </div>

    <blockquote class="pullquote pullquote--center">
      That's not a philosophy. It's physiology.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        Everything named above — the cycling, the failed protocols, the 2 a.m. body that won't stand
        down, the diagnosis that explained everything and changed nothing — points to the same gap:
        nobody ever gave you tools that work at the level where the activation actually lives. The
        <strong>Nervous System Regulation Protocol — Six Pillars, Seven Tools, Thirty Days</strong>
        is the direct answer to that gap. Not a framework for understanding your trauma. A working
        toolkit for regulating the system that's been carrying it.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="subhead">The Three Phases</h3>
    <div class="pillars">
      <% const phases = [
        ['1','PHASE 1 — CONTACT','You prove to yourself on Day 1 that your nervous system can be reached — using the 90-Second Reset, a single tool that produces a measurable physiological shift before you\'ve read anything else. Contact first. Theory after.'],
        ['2','PHASE 2 — REGULATION','You work through six structured pillars that build your capacity to recognize activation states and move through them deliberately — so you\'re no longer at the mercy of a system that doesn\'t know the mission ended.'],
        ['3','PHASE 3 — INTEGRATION','You build a repeatable daily practice from the seven tools — one that travels with you, requires no appointment, and doesn\'t depend on someone else being in the room.']
      ]; %>
      <% phases.forEach(function(p){ %>
        <article class="pillar reveal">
          <div class="pillar__badge"><%= p[0] %></div>
          <h3 class="pillar__name"><%= p[1] %></h3>
          <p class="pillar__desc"><%= p[2] %></p>
        </article>
      <% }); %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ THE SIX PILLARS (supporting detail) ============ -->
<section class="section pillars-section reveal" id="whats-inside">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="label">INSIDE PHASE 2 — REGULATION</p>
    <h2 class="display">Six Pillars. Thirty Days. One Working Kit.</h2>

    <div class="pillars">
      <% const pillars = [
        ['1','ORIENT','The 90-Second Reset. Prove to yourself on Day 1 that your nervous system can be reached.'],
        ['2','ASSESS','The Symptom-to-Tool Triage Chart. Match the right tool to the right symptom in real time.'],
        ['3','EQUIP','The Seven-Tool Kit. Your full arsenal. Know which three are yours.'],
        ['4','EXECUTE','The 45-Minute Operator System. Stop running a 12-hour shift. Run sixteen 45-minute operations.'],
        ['5','SUSTAIN','The Two-Sentence Containment Practice. Rebuild the wire between mission and home.'],
        ['6','ADAPT','The Personal Field Update. Your monthly after-action review. The kit gets sharper every cycle.']
      ]; %>
      <% pillars.forEach(function(p){ %>
        <article class="pillar reveal">
          <div class="pillar__badge"><%= p[0] %></div>
          <h3 class="pillar__name">PILLAR <%= p[0] %> — <%= p[1] %></h3>
          <p class="pillar__desc"><%= p[2] %></p>
        </article>
      <% }); %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ THE SEVEN TOOLS (supporting detail) ============ -->
<section class="section tools-section reveal" id="tools">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="label">THE TOOLKIT</p>
    <h2 class="display">Seven Tools. Pick Three. Carry Three. Master Three.</h2>

    <ol class="tools">
      <% const tools = [
        ['90-Second Visual Orienting Reset','Baseline tension, pre-shift dread'],
        ['Long Exhale Stack (4-in / 8-out)','0300 wake-up, sleep, anxiety spike'],
        ['Box Breathing (4-4-4-4)','Pre-shift, focus reset, pre-confrontation'],
        ['5-4-3-2-1 Sensory Grounding','Irritability, dissociation, spiral'],
        ['Physical Contact Drill','Dissociation, numbness, floating'],
        ['Bilateral Movement Drill','Brain fog, stuck, transitions'],
        ['One-Sentence Containment Write','End of shift, before bed']
      ]; %>
      <% tools.forEach(function(t, i){ %>
        <li class="tool reveal">
          <span class="tool__num"><%= i + 1 %></span>
          <div class="tool__body">
            <h3 class="tool__name"><%= t[0] %></h3>
            <p class="tool__use"><%= t[1] %></p>
          </div>
        </li>
      <% }); %>
    </ol>

    <blockquote class="pullquote pullquote--center">
      "When in doubt, run Tool 1. Always free. Always works."
    </blockquote>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ ZONE 4 — PROOF & FILTER ============ -->
<section class="section proof-section reveal" id="proof">
  <div class="container container--narrow">
    <p class="label">PROOF &amp; FILTER</p>
    <h2 class="display">The Proof Structure — and Who This Is For.</h2>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        No specific client outcome numbers are published on this page. What is verifiable: the
        90-Second Reset is drawn from peer-reviewed polyvagal and somatic research, and the protocol
        is built on tools with documented clinical application — not proprietary theory. Day 1
        produces a measurable shift or the guarantee activates. That's the proof structure here.
      </p>
      <p><strong>This is for you if:</strong></p>
    </div>

    <ul class="checklist">
      <% const forYou = [
        'You separated from service and your body still hasn\'t — you\'re home but you\'re not present, and you\'ve been trying to explain that gap to people who\'ve never felt it',
        'You\'ve been through the VA or private care rotation — diagnosis, medication, referral, repeat — and you\'re still carrying the same weight you walked in with',
        'You know what hypervigilance feels like from the inside, not as a clinical term but as a full-time job your body never clocks out of',
        'You got a diagnosis that named it correctly but didn\'t change it, and you\'re still looking for the part where something actually shifts',
        'You\'re functional — still standing, still working, still showing up — but you\'re exhausted by the cost of holding it together, and you know the current approach isn\'t it'
      ]; %>
      <% forYou.forEach(function(f){ %>
        <li class="check reveal"><span class="check__mark">✓</span><span><%= f %></span></li>
      <% }); %>
    </ul>

    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:36px">
      <p><strong>This is NOT for you if:</strong></p>
    </div>

    <ul class="checklist">
      <% const notForYou = [
        'You are currently in crisis and need immediate clinical intervention — this is not that, and it is not a substitute for it',
        'You are looking for a licensed mental health treatment program — this is a self-directed somatic toolkit, not clinical care',
        'You want a passive read that explains your nervous system without asking you to use the tools',
        'You are unwilling to work directly with physical sensation — this protocol operates at the body level, and that is non-negotiable'
      ]; %>
      <% notForYou.forEach(function(n){ %>
        <li class="check check--no reveal"><span class="check__mark">✕</span><span><%= n %></span></li>
      <% }); %>
    </ul>

    <div class="prose" style="margin-top:40px">
      <p>
        I didn't build this from a case study or a certification alone. I built it because I was the
        person cycling through the appointments, collecting the diagnoses, and leaving every session
        with the same body I brought in. What I eventually realized wasn't a breakthrough insight — it
        was a missing layer: nobody had ever worked with me at the level where the activation actually
        lived. What I built is the toolkit I couldn't find when I needed it.
      </p>
      <p class="letter__sign">Bobby L. Harris</p>
      <p class="letter__creds">
        FMF Navy Corpsman (2002–2009) &nbsp;|&nbsp; OEF Veteran &nbsp;|&nbsp; Founder, Battlefield Essentials
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

